description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic Band 6 nurse who will strive for high standards of patient care to join our team of highly professional cancer nurses. The role is based at the Sussex Cancer Centre, Royal Sussex County Hospital, Brighton and will occasionally involve working at our sister unit at Hurstwood Park Haematology/Oncology day unit, Princess Royal Hospital. You will work in the Cancer Treatment Unit, giving SACT, mentoring junior staff and running Nurse led clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post requires that you have skills including venepuncture, cannulation, central line care and a good understanding of the management of patients in an outpatient setting. You will have a sound knowledge of oncology and/or haematology as well as the knowledge and skills required to safely manage patients receiving systemic anti-cancer therapies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return you will be supported to further enhance both your clinical and leadership skills and given opportunities for professional development within a progressive team, where your nursing skills will be highly valued by patients, their families and the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in cancer nursing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Haematology or Oncology pathway or equivalent post registration qualification in cancer care (desirable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intravenous cytotoxic administration skills(essential for band 6)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cannulation, Venepuncture skills (essential band 6)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PICC line placement (desirable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Emma Hartwell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Nurse Manger of Sussex Cancer Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address bsuh.scc.nurse.manager@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01273 696955 ext 3585&lt;/p&gt;
